==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uvitic
<hw>U*vit"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>uva</ets> a grape. So called because it may be produced indirectly
from tartaric acid, which is found in the grape.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid,
<chform>CH3C6H3(CO2H)2</chform>, obtained as a white crystalline
substance by the partial oxidation of mesitylene; -- called also
<xex>mesitic acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uvitonic</ent>⟦br⟧
